        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 8 at 3:06PM EDT by NWS Gaylord MI</headline>
        <description>At 306 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Royston, or 13 miles northeast of Atlanta, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lachine, Long Rapids, Hillman, Royston, and Spratt.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
